      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in FDA's guidance on spinal implant testing. Each maps directly to a clinical failure mode: stiffness to subsidence risk, yield force to intraoperative fracture, and force at 40 mm to fatigue life surrogate. Relevance chain documented in the model description document."
